          <div class="faq-answer-inner">Metal roofing can be slightly louder during heavy rain compared to shingles, but the difference is minimal when properly installed. A quality synthetic underlayment, solid roof decking, and attic insulation absorb most of the sound. In practice, most Tampa Bay homeowners with metal roofs report that rain noise is not an issue and is actually less noticeable than they expected before installation.</div>
